SHELL (
Fig. 85
; 
Tables 3–4
). Depressed conical, with 5.25–5.5 slightly convex whorls; protoconch almost smooth; teleoconch with fine, irregular wrinkles; apical side with indistinct incised spiral lines, umbilical side with more distinct spiral lines; scaly processes not observed; tuberculate around umbilicus; whitish with a reddish-brown band at periphery; body whorl angular; aperture oval; upper insertion of peristome slightly descending; peristome expanded, reflexed and thickened; umbilicus eccentric, wide, comprising 24–30% of shell diameter, hardly obscured by columellar edge.
